Class Animal

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.image.ImageView
p4_group_8_repo.Actor
p4_group_8_repo.Animal
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget, ImageGenerator
public class Animal
extends Actor

Animal is the player's Avatar in the game, which in this case is the Frog.

Animal is also an Actor.

It can move. It might get hit by the obstacles on the road or drown in the river and die.

Its goal is to reach the empty End on the other side.

User

  • Constructor Details

    • Animal

      public Animal​(java.lang.String imageLink)
      This constructor will create an Animal object. Its initial position in the game is set.
      The Animal can now move up (W key) down (S key) left (A key) and right (D key) with different animations. This is done by implementing setOnKeyPressed and setOnKeyReleased to detect and handle the keyboard inputs.
      Parameters:
      imageLink - The image link for how the Animal is displayed in the game

  • Method Details

    • animalAnimationSetUp

      public void animalAnimationSetUp()
      Sets up all the necessary animations and looks for the Animal.
      Images for the animations are set up by calling createImage(String) method

    • act

      public void act​(long now)
      defines how Actor would act in the Game.
      It will be called every once per frame while the Actor and the Game are active.
      Defines how Animal will behave in the game.
      Animal can collide with other game objects and move along with them. Should the Animal experience any car death, water death or monster death. Animal will perform relevant actions upon its death.
      Deaths are determined upon calling methods :checkcarDeath(boolean, long) checkwaterDeath(boolean, long), checkmonsterDeath(boolean, long)
      Should the Animal successfully reach the destinations, Animal will get points.
      If Animal is moves out of the game scene, Animal will be moved back.
      Specified by:
      act in class Actor
      Parameters:
      now - in nanoseconds format and it represents the timestamp of the current frame.

    • checkmonsterDeath

      public void checkmonsterDeath​(boolean mD, long now)
      Checks if Animal gets eaten by the Monster and performs relevant actions.
      Should the Animal experience a monster death, Animal will be deducted 10points.
      Parameters:
      mD - monsterDeath
      now - current time frame in nanoseconds
